## üßÆ Numeric comparison

Use **`if`** with **`lss`**, **`leq`**, **`equ`**, **`neq`**, **`gtr`**, or **`geq`**
(no angle brackets ‚Äî those are reserved by the shell).

| Comparison | Meaning               |
| ---------- | --------------------- |
| `LSS`      | less than             |
| `LEQ`      | less than or equal    |
| `EQU`      | equal                 |
| `NEQ`      | not equal             |
| `GTR`      | greater than          |
| `GEQ`      | greater than or equal |

---

### Example:

```bat
@echo off
set /a num=7

if %num% lss 10 (
    echo %num% is less than 10
)

if %num% gtr 5 (
    echo %num% is greater than 5
)

if %num% equ 7 (
    echo %num% equals 7
)
```

‚úÖ Works fine for integers
‚ùå Won‚Äôt handle decimals (you‚Äôll need PowerShell or a trick for that)

