## üß© String comparison

For *text*, use normal `==`:

```bat
set var=hello

if "%var%"=="hello" echo It matches!
if not "%var%"=="goodbye" echo It‚Äôs not goodbye.
```

You can still combine this with `/i` for case-insensitive compare:

```bat
if /i "%var%"=="HELLO" echo It still matches.
```

